## Project Overview

**{{PROJECT_NAME}}** - {{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}

Uses **Harmony AI Framework** with Guardian Protocol, HQVF Quality, and Sentinel Memory.

## Essential Commands

```bash
/go                        # Session kickoff - ALWAYS run first
/harmony                   # Interactive menu (30 commands)
/harmony quick             # Fast validation (~30s)
/harmony full              # Complete audit (~2-5 min)
/harmony sentinel          # Error memory dashboard
/harmony sentinel --reset  # Reset circuit breaker if OPEN
```

## Before Starting Work

1. Check `.harmony/memory/workflow-state.json` for current phase (1-5)
2. Verify a story exists before coding (Guardian enforced)
3. Run `/harmony quick` after changes

## Discovery Phase (Phase 1)

If in Discovery phase, focus on:
- **Problem elicitation** - Understand the problem domain
- **Stakeholder analysis** - Identify users and their needs
- **Context gathering** - Explore constraints and requirements
- **Product brief creation** - Document findings

Keywords: analyze, requirement, understand, explore, research

## Key Rules

| Rule | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **No code without story** | Guardian blocks unauthorized changes |
| **UCV required** | Stories need Use Case Verifications |
| **Circuit breaker** | 3 failures = OPEN, needs reset |

## Architecture

```
.harmony/
├── agents/           # Agent definitions (Developer, Tester, Analyst...)
├── workflows/        # Phase workflows (1-analysis to 5-maintenance)
├── rules/            # Validation rules (R-*.yaml)
├── hooks/            # Pre/post validation scripts
│   ├── guardian-checkpoint.sh
│   ├── sentinel-pre.sh
│   └── sentinel-post.sh
├── specialties/      # Domain expertise modules
│   ├── gaming/       # Game mechanics, leaderboards
│   ├── security/     # OWASP, pentesting
│   ├── ai/           # RAG, LLM, memory
│   └── ...           # accessibility, devops, i18n, mobile, quality
├── memory/           # Sentinel memory files
│   ├── workflow-state.json
│   ├── circuit-breaker.json
│   └── error-journal.json
└── README.md         # Full documentation (30 commands)
```

